         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/8/69 ¶  ¶ Since I saw you, dear Sir Redmond, I have put several vegetable substances into order for the new industrial museum, ¶ Barry had requested items for display in R. Barry to M, 3 August 186...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.08.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Redmond Barry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">VPRS 5486/PO/4, official inward correspondence, VA 928 Melbourne Public Library, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/8/69</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since I saw you, dear Sir Redmond, I have put several vegetable substances into order for the new industrial museum,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Barry had requested items for display in R. Barry to M, 3 August 1869.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but, I am very much in want of glasses with a wide orifice, so need as many glass frames and glass-cases, as are obtainable.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It seems there are many glass-cases, which might be emptied in the Exhib. Building, and if so, I would eagerly seize on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">any</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>such case. I further would recommend that some printed labels be got for tickets to the objects. How are these to be obtained? Will the trustees make an advance? or will the trustees give me authority to have them ordered and the account within a limited sum be rendered to them? Some methodus operandi will need to be adopted, and as I really can not afford the time to go much to &amp; fro without necessity.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On Wednesday I have to attend a council meeting of the board of Agriculture and I can after that come to the Exhibition-Building to receive any glassces,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M has left out some letters in going from one line to the next.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which may become empty. I will ask my colleagues also allow the whole agricultural collection &amp; the soils-samples to pass into the general industrial collection<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to R. Barry, 2 September 1869.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With very regardful salutation your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
